WEBVTT

00:11:27.833 --> 00:11:30.167
and I said, "We agree with you."

00:11:31.083 --> 00:11:34.351
And I said, "How about working together?"

00:11:34.375 --> 00:11:37.018
So three days later,

00:11:37.042 --> 00:11:39.226
miraculously, four people from McDonald's,

00:11:39.250 --> 00:11:40.726
four people from Greenpeace,

00:11:40.750 --> 00:11:43.518
we're meeting in the London
Heathrow airport.

00:11:43.542 --> 00:11:46.476
And I have to say,
the first hour was shaky,

00:11:46.500 --> 00:11:48.851
it wasn't a whole lot
of trust in the room.

00:11:48.875 --> 00:11:52.059
But it seemed like
everything came together,

00:11:52.083 --> 00:11:56.559
because each of us
wanted to save the Amazon.

00:11:56.583 --> 00:11:57.934
And during our discussions,

00:11:57.958 --> 00:12:00.226
you couldn't really tell, I don't think,